<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-09-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="16" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d16">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Prince <persName type="from">Ferdinand</persName> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-09-19"><hi rend="italic">September 19,
                                    1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>It was with a real pleasure, especially in these sad times, that I
                            received to-day from Mr. John Brinckerhoff Jackson your autograph
                            letter. I am very content at the friendly and cordial feelings you
                            transmit by him to myself and to my Government, and I hope that the good
                            relations between the two countries shall still be more strengthened in
                            the future.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ferdinand.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>